📦 SBOM & Vulnerability Scan Script

This script generates:

SBOM using Syft
Vulnerability report using Trivy

for a given container image.

🛠 Requirements

Make sure these are installed:

syft
trivy
bash
▶️ Usage

Make script executable:

chmod +x generate-reports.sh

Run the script:

./generate-reports.sh <image-name>

Example:

./generate-reports.sh ubuntu:22.04
📂 Output

The script creates:

sbom.json → SBOM report
trivy-report.json → vulnerability report
🧠 What it does
Takes an image name as input
Generates SBOM using Syft
Runs Trivy scan on the image
Saves both results as JSON files
⚠️ Notes
Script will exit if:
No image is provided
Syft or Trivy is not installed
🎯 Purpose

Useful for:

DevSecOps practice
CI/CD pipeline integration
Basic container security analysis